  "title": "Designer",
  "description": "<p>Job Description & RequirementsPrepare technical drawings, section, and details as per requirement</p><p>Design plans using computer-aided design, draughting (CAD) software.</p><p>Draft and prepare layout drawings.</p><p>Collaborate with Designer, Contractors, Operations and Project Managers on Projects.</p><p>Revise drawings and layout to accommodate changes and enhancement.</p><p>Able to organize, lead and chair meetings with operations team to understand operational requirements and draft out test fit.</p><p>Prepare as-built drawings for submission.</p><p>Assist the project team in combining all information trades in drawing</p><p>Responsible for checking the correctness of trade information</p><p>Draw, coordinates and monitor shop drawings submission schedule</p><p>Able to perform 3D rendering for visualization and photoshop for image editing</p><p>Alerts project team for any changes or clashes of various trades and services</p><p>Ensure design system comply with the code requirements</p><p>Preparation of drawings and compile documents for submission</p><p>Coordinate with project team for details based on required standard</p><p>Draw structural drawing as per required standard</p><p>Ensure all drawings are checked and approved</p><p>Perform field work if needed, to measure and sketch existing or proposed sites</p><p>Documentation as per project requirement</p><p>Perform other duties as assigned by the superior</p><p>Ensure all drawings are in accordance with the standards set by company’s quality</p><p>Rectify and update latest drawing accordance to changes</p><p>Candidate must possess at least Diploma/Advanced/Higher/Graduate Diploma in Others or equivalent.</p><p>MUST BE PROFICIENT in 3D MAX, AUTOCAD 2D 3D, REVIT, SKETCH UP & Photoshop (COMPULSORY)</p><p>Strong Knowledge / well versed in 3D Max, 2D 3D, Revit, & Photoshop</p><p>At least 3-5 year(s) of working experiences in the related field is required for this position.</p><p>Proficient in English and good verbal communication skills is desired</p><p>Preferably with experience in consultancy firm of construction industry</p><p>Conversant in Authorities’ regulations and submission processes</p><p>Preferably Senior Executives spe</p><p>4 off days monthly, rest days depend on schedule</p><p>able to work long hours and late in evenings and weekends</p><p>If you have an interest in applying for this role, please WhatsApp me at 98198786 to apply. Only shortlisted candidates will be notified. Priority will be given to Singaporeans</p><p>Young hon Lim/ manager</p><p>Render private limited</p><p>EA licence no 15c7827</p><p>EA reg no R1550906</p>",
